mindmap
  root((AI Strategic Map))
    Why It Matters
      Closes the gap between execution and alignment
      Creates transparency that builds trust
      Enables prioritization through strategic themes
      Transforms isolated projects into a coordinated portfolio
    Five Building Blocks
      Business Goals - specific, measurable, current
      Transformation Themes - organizing pillars of change
      AI Initiatives - linked to outcomes with owners and timelines
      Dependencies and Enablers - infrastructure, talent, governance
      Measurement Framework - KPIs tied to business impact
    Portfolio Architecture
      Organize by transformation theme
      Classify by maturity stage - discovery, pilot, scale, embedded
      Balance short-term wins with long-term bets
      Surface interdependencies across initiatives
      Align talent to lifecycle stages
    Governance and Accountability
      Executive sponsors for each theme
      Named business and technical owners per initiative
      Shared success metrics visible on the map
      Quarterly cross-functional reviews
      Consequences, recognition, and course correction
    Living System
      Review quarterly at planned intervals
      Revisit in response to emergent triggers
      Evolve as maturity grows - add enablers and policy layers
      Use for communication - town halls, board updates, recruiting
      Mirror of organizational transformation progress